Twisting the staff would release a great burst of energy that negated magic around it.

Stuffed with tomes of all shapes and sizes, this bookcase stores a wealth of knowledge. However, the frames appear splattered in blood and you begin to wonder of the words bound within the black leather of the books sitting upon these shelves!

Graz'zt, The Demon lord. By Macros Darksun

Standing nine feet tall, Graz'zt appears as a lithe, muscular humanoid. His skin shines like polished obsidian, and his eyes glitter with malevolent green light. He has yellowed fangs, pointed ears, and six slender fingers decorating each hand. 

He is sometimes described as having six small black horns half hidden amid his thick black hair. His fiendish traits are apparent and regardless of whatever form Graz'zt chooses to take, he's considered the comeliest demon in the Abyss. He also dresses in the most expensive and elegant finery to be found on the plane. He wields an acid-drenched great sword in one hand and a profane tower shield in the other, and thus this dark prince is a veritable killing machine when loosed upon the hordes of the Abyss and adventurers alike.

What's more he has a vast repertoire of spells at his disposal, which makes him a deadly magical opponent as well. However, Graz'zt's greatest weapons are his mastery of seduction and guile. He entertains the notion that he's the most cunning and intelligent creature in the Abyss; indeed, there are few who could possibly contest such a claim.

Paush, Demon Lord of Zanshibon. By Macros Darksun

Paush, Standing a good 9 feet tall, with blood red skin and hair that shines black like ebony. His scepter of power glows with an unholy light. His horns extending out a fair meter, polished and sharpened. He possesses a massive muscled body a true testament to his demonic heritage. With a tail that extends meters behind him, and cloven hooves he appears much the Demon Lord of Zanshibon.

Lord Paush who styles himself as a high priest or god in his city, rules Zanshibon with an iron fist, yet the citizens seems comfortable under his steadfast rule, every one of them a dying servant till the last. His persuasive manner and polite curiosity a true boon to his cause.

Lord Paush possessing mighty magical arts is no stranger to the field of battle, leading troops into the blood wars many times in his past. Now he seeks others to assist him in that cause, drawing adventurers of capable skill down to his home. Many choose to leave, others stay and fight, reaping the rewards of battle.

Paush keeps a close eye on his people, making sure all love and serve him, those who do not are quickly dispatched by his tiefling guards. Through this system he creates an entire plane of loyal and powerful servants to charge into the blood wars in honor of their master.

Yet, Paush while magnificent is weakening, no one knows why, he can no longer battle in the blood wars, preferring to remain behind in his citadel, accompanied by his many succubae. Perhaps in our lifetimes we will know what has weakened the once wholly powerful demonic lord of Chaos, Paush.

The Blood Pact - by Macros Darksun

The blood pact, a ritual surrounded in mystery, an act taken by only the most desperate and greedy. It is the act of selling yourself to a demon, yet the demon must also pay you something in return. Many servants of evil take this route to gain wickedly powers, forgetting that a demon rarely gives away power without knowing that you can't use it against him.

The act of making a blood pact is simple; you need a virgin dagger - A blade that has never killed.

First slice a cross shape into your hand, and then have the demon do the same. Now clasp hands and let your blood mingle: the sensation of your hand being burnt off should occur after a short while.

Now, the blood pact is complete. Breaking a blood pact will leave you severely weakened. Only reinstating the pact will regain your power.

The Regalia of Evil - by Macros Darksun

The regalia of evil are a collection of armors and weapons so profane that records of it in many places have been destroyed by holy warriors. Skimming the preamble you find out the following:

It's composed of:

- A bastard sword, with a serrated edge, a black leather handle, and a hilt made of silver. This sword apparently bursts with hellfire before combat, and negative energy infused with fire makes the sword a weapon to be feared by many.

- A single gauntlet, possessing the ability to crush and grind steel to dust. The crafting of this gauntlet has never been found, though many claim to own it, however none of the claims have proven true.

- A large tower shield formed from an obsidian rock and which pulsates with a shadowy light. This shield is most coveted by the denizens of the Abyss and imparts a wickedly defense in combat.

- A helmet though more of a mask to those who would use it. It covers the face and has eye slits but it's unknown to what magical powers it possesses.

- An armor of segmented plates that ooze thoughts of evil. Nobody living has ever seen it and has lived to tell the tale, so whispers are all that tell of its existence.

The Trident of Power by Macros Darksun.

The Trident of Power sometimes named the Nefarious Fork of Doom was owned by the arch-demon Archemodeus, once ruler of the 432nd layer of the Abyss, and grand master of life and death over his subjects. His fork fueled his power and he almost never let it leave his hand. The power of his fork allowed him to read his subjects' minds, and to control them at will. Therefore it was a powerful artifact, and no one but Archemodeus knew of its making.
 
The fork has now become a scepter of power for the 432nd layer. He who possesses it, also possesses the layer's inhabitants. While Archemodeus is locked away in a dimensional prison, his Trident is hidden so none might find it. The fork itself is described as being around 12ft long with three barbed prongs sprouting from it's tip. It radiates magnificent thoughts of evil, yet while held it's power does not radiate from the fork itself, rather from the wielder. While on the 432nd layer, many creatures, both good and evil, long to grip it's shaft yet little do they realize that they merely become a vassal for it's unholy powers.

Demon Summoning - Anonymous.

The process that's involved here is dangerous and an ultimate evil. Its sheer act can drive a man to tears. My work will be sent to Eliminster the Mage so that he may ponder my findings. The components used here are rare and terribly expensive, and cannot be found in any local apothecary. 

Stage one:
Draw the standard summoning symbol on the ground; be careful to not leave out any of the detail. [Disc illustration provided.]

Stage two:
Set up braziers in a star shape around the summoning circle; place one exactly in the center of the circle.

Stage three: 
Place your components of magical uses in the brazier, I used a bloodstone but other components include a rakshasa's eye or some dragon's blood.

Stage three: 
Light the surrounding braziers with normal fire; magical fire will harm the demon, so light the component with magical fire. Do NOT use holy fire.

Stage four: 
Cast circle against evil on yourself, then the demon won't perceive you as a threat. If you do not cast this spell the summoned may become enraged by your presence.

Anecdote:
I have now summoned a demon, it'll arrive within the hour, and these notes are almost finished. I shall send this to the Archmage as soon as I'm done here. Before I forget though I shall now cast Protection against Evil to… (The writing ends here and all that remains are splattered bloodstains.)
This black leatherbound book simply has no title, just a large red bloodstain.

The 363rd Layer- By Macros Darksun

The 363rd layer, ruled by Paush the Almighty. It is a vast desert like place, being filled with deep crevasses and pits, pillars of flame rising up into the red clouds that adorn the sky. The abyssal city of Zanshibon is the only landmark for miles around, standing tall and proud amid the ravages of the blood wars that rage around it. Zanshibon is ruled by an arch demon of massive power, Paush, who sometimes lures adventurers from the isle of Amia to battle in his war for riches and power. This layer is also home to many other powerful demons; mostly all soldiers of the Blood Wars who will attack at a whim's notice. My warning is to be especially cautious here for the demons watch from every corner here.
